🛡️ Why Use .env.example?
Keeps credentials like database passwords out of version control (e.g., GitHub)

Allows others to know what values they need to configure

Works well with libraries like python-dotenv or frameworks that load env variables




# .env.example

# 🔐 Database Configuration
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=3306
DB_USER=your_username
DB_PASSWORD=your_password
DB_NAME=employee_db

# 🔧 Flask App Configuration
FLASK_ENV=development
SECRET_KEY=your_flask_secret_key
